======================================================================
PHASE 1, DOMAIN 3: BOHR-SOMMERFELD
Harmonic Oscillator in Exact Fraction Arithmetic
======================================================================

(a) STANDARD FORM

  Bohr-Sommerfeld quantization:
    ∮ p·dq = 2πℏ(n + μ/4)

  Harmonic oscillator V(x) = (1/2)mω²x²:
    Classical turning points at x = ±A, where E = (1/2)mω²A²
    Action: ∮ p·dq = ∮ √(2m(E - V)) dx = 2πE/ω
    Quantization: 2πE/ω = 2πℏ(n + μ/4)
    Therefore: E_n = ℏω(n + μ/4)

  Maslov index μ = 2 (two soft turning points, each +1)
  Therefore: E_n = ℏω(n + 1/2)

(b) DECOMPOSED: INTEGER QUOTIENT + REMAINDER

  E_n / (ℏω) = n + 1/2

  Modulus: ℏω (one energy quantum)
  Integer: n (quantum number, counts nodes)
  Remainder: 1/2 (Maslov correction from turning points)

  The remainder 1/2 is:
    - Topologically determined (μ counts turning point types)
    - Independent of n (same correction at every level)
    - Physically observable (zero-point energy E_0 = ℏω/2)
    - Rational (exact Fraction 1/2, no transcendental)

(c) FRACTION ARITHMETIC COMPUTATION

  Parameters (natural units):
    ℏ = 1
    ω = 1
    Modulus ℏω = 1
    Maslov index μ = 2
    Maslov correction μ/4 = 1/2

  Energy levels E_n = ℏω(n + 1/2):
